HEADWORD: Alure
<hw>Al"ure</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>alure</ets>, <ets>aleure</ets>, walk, gait, fr. <ets>aler</ets> (F.
<ets>aller</ets>) to go.]</ety> <def>A walk or passage; -- applied to
passages of various kinds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sides of every street were covered with fresh
<qex>alures</qex> of marble.</q> <rj><qau>T. Warton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alutaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
